                            <comment id="16679186" author="udim" created="Thu, 8 Nov 2018 02:13:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Peeking at the code in MoreExecutors.java, addDelayedShutdownHook() doesn&apos;t save the reference to the thread it creates, so it won&apos;t be easy to remove the hook.&lt;br/&gt;
The solution I&apos;m looking at is to use a single persistent thread pool executeBatches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
